    "The remaining samples were utilized for training.",
    "Subsequently, we randomly extracted 20% samples from the D1 dataset to create an unbalanced independent validation set (Unbvalidation set), while the remaining samples served as the training set.",
    "The experimental results on these two independent validation sets are summarized in Table 6.We assessed the model's performance on the two independent validation sets in comparison to its performance on the benchmark dataset.",
    "Notably, there was a decrease in performance on the independent validation sets, specifically in terms of the two primary metrics, AUC and AUPR.",
    "Despite this decrease, the model still demonstrated relatively good results."
